menu "Live Ninja IoT (ln_iot)"

    config LN_IOT_TOPIC_PREFIX
        string "Application MQTT topic prefix"
        default "liveninja"
        help
            Prefix for application topics: <prefix>/<thingName>/control/up|down and
            <prefix>/<thingName>/telemetry. Must match the per-device IoT policy
            provisioned by the backend (contracts/shadow.md, plan.md M5).

    config LN_IOT_PROV_TEMPLATE
        string "Default fleet provisioning template name"
        default "liveninja-tab5"
        help
            Used when the pairing flow did not store a template name in NVS.
            Must match the Fleet Provisioning template created by WS-A (M0
            "IoT Core baseline").

    config LN_IOT_HEARTBEAT_S
        int "Telemetry heartbeat interval (seconds)"
        default 30
        range 5 3600
        help
            device_heartbeat cadence on liveninja/<thing>/telemetry (rssi, free
            heap, app state, firmware version).

    config LN_IOT_MQTT_BUF_SIZE
        int "MQTT rx/tx buffer size (bytes)"
        default 8192
        range 2048 32768
        help
            Sized so fleet-provisioning responses (certificate PEM ~1.3KB inside
            JSON) and full shadow documents arrive without chunking; chunked
            reassembly is still handled if a payload exceeds this.

    config LN_IOT_VERIFY_TIMEOUT_S
        int "OTA rollback watchdog (seconds)"
        default 300
        range 60 3600
        help
            After booting an unverified (pending-verify) OTA image, the firmware
            must complete an MQTT connect to AWS IoT within this window or it
            calls esp_ota_mark_app_invalid_rollback_and_reboot().

endmenu
